BEGIN_PGML
The first step for solving each equation below is _incorrect_. Replace it with the correct step.
a.  [$NBSP]*

    [```\newcommand{\blert}[1]{\boldsymbol{\color{blue}{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
    \begin{aligned}
    6(5^{3t})\amp=20\\
    \color{gray}{(\log 6)(\log 5^{3t})}\amp=\color{gray}{\log {20}}\amp\amp \blert{\text{(Wrong!)}}
    \end{aligned}
    ```]

    Instead, the first step should be

    [_]{$a}{5}

a.  [$NBSP]*

    [```\newcommand{\blert}[1]{\boldsymbol{\color{blue}{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
    \begin{aligned}
    t \log 8\amp=\log{53}\\
    \color{gray}{t}\amp=\color{gray}{\log {\dfrac{53}{8}}}\amp\amp \blert{\text{(Wrong!)}}
    \end{aligned}
    ```]

    Instead, the first step should be

    [_]{$b}{5}

a.  [$NBSP]*

    [```\newcommand{\blert}[1]{\boldsymbol{\color{blue}{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
    \begin{aligned}
    12(10)^{-0.06t}\amp=192\\
    \color{gray}{120^{-0.06t}}\amp=\color{gray}{192}\amp\amp \blert{\text{(Wrong!)}}
    \end{aligned}
    ```]

    Instead, the first step should be

    [_]{$c}{5}

a.  [$NBSP]*

    [```\newcommand{\blert}[1]{\boldsymbol{\color{blue}{#1}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
    \begin{aligned}
    \log x +\log {(x-2)}\amp=3 \\
    \color{gray}{x + (x-2)}\amp=\color{gray}{10^3}\amp\amp \blert{\text{(Wrong!)}}
    \end{aligned}
    ```]

    Instead, the first step should be

    [_]{$d}{5}

END_PGML

