############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context(Point)->flags->set( reduceConstants => 0, reduceConstantFunctions => 0, ); $a = Formula("x^2/8 - y^2/2"); $hyperbola = PopUp( ["?","a circle", "an ellipse", "a hyperbola", "a parabola"], 3, ); $origin = Point(0,0); $vertices = Formula("(-2*sqrt(2),0), (2*sqrt(2),0)"); $my_evaluator = $vertices -> cmp( showHints=>1, showLengthHints => 1, partialCredit => 1, ); $are = PopUp( ["?","are", "are not"], 1, ); $slope = Formula("1/2 *x");
$b = Formula("-4x^2"); $parabola = PopUp( ["?","a circle", "an ellipse", "a hyperbola", "a parabola"], 4, ); $down = PopUp( ["?","left", "right", "upward", "downward"], 4, );
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Write each equation in standard form and describe its graph. a. [`4y^2=x^2-8`]
Standard form: [_]{$a}{15}[`=1`]
The graph is [_]{$hyperbola}{5} centered at the point [_]{$origin}{5}, with vertices [_]{$my_evaluator}{25}. There [_]{$are}{5} asymptotes: [`y=\pm`][_]{$slope}{3}.
a. [`4x^2+y=0`]
Standard form: [`y=`][_]{$b}{15}
The graph is [_]{$parabola}{5} with vertex at the point [_]{$origin}{5}, opening [_]{$down}{5}.
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`\dfrac{x^2}{8}-\dfrac{y^2}{2}=1 \text{.}`] A hyperbola centered at the origin with vertices [`\left(2\sqrt{2},0 \right) `] and [`\left(-2\sqrt{2},0 \right) \text{,}`] and asymptotes [`y = \dfrac{1}{2}x`] and [`y = -\dfrac{1}{2} x\text{.}`]
a. [`y=-4x^2\text{.}`] A parabola opening downward with vertex at the origin.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
